I wasn't surprised to see that she is from the US and has song writing credits on many of their hits even though that is rare in the k-pop industry. She is a very creative person and I hope that she has a long successful career!

JELLYFISH OUT NOW
#HUHYUNJIN_jellyfish

author: @sairrrin
text:
From Jellyfish’s album intro on Melon 🪼
“Yunjin drew inspiration for the song from jellyfish, who live their lives swimming through rough seas. In her view, jellyfish are creatures who don’t even have hearts, but live being carried along by the harsh waters. Despite the tough environments, jellyfish simply do its best to survive. Offering an unexpected sense of comfort, a feeling which Yunjin then blended into her song.

…The lyrics, "Jellyfish, why don't you know / How beautiful you are /
You're busy breathing, I'll appreciate you in your stead", offer comfort to those who are working hard living out their lives. Just as the jellyfish provided her with comfort, Yunjin hopes this song will bring the same emotion to listeners.”
